data.job_description:
MAY 30, 2022

Scellus is a technology agency based in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia. We focus on solving problems to produce intelligent designs, deliver engaging experiences and build meaningful connections.

In order to create even better digital products, tools, solutions and applications that will help our partners and clients achieve progress, we’re going to strengthen and expand the expertise of our Digital Design team.

We are looking for an energetic, confident and organized Full Stack Web Developer with at least 2 years experience to develop and produce visually beautiful designs for our clients and projects. You will support the Digital Design team in an array of projects and must be able to take a job from concept through final production in a fast-paced environment and ensuring good quality design. You are self-motivated, pay close attention to detail, and able to manage multiple projects at once.

We’re also flexible if you need to work from home when required.

Roles & responsibilities.
• Work within the creative team to create and produce innovative web design solutions for clients.
• An intimate understating of design and content practices.
• PHP-based website production, coding, deployment, and optimization of ongoing projects.
• Optimize applications for speed and scalability.
• Development of front-end and back-end web properties, working closely with our creative team to develop, implement, and maintain designs that fit our brand look and feel.
• Lightweight server-side maintenance (domains, DNS, redirects, hosting specially on AWS).
• Plan & execute the projects from start to completion involving deadlines, milestones and processes.
• Package management and frontend build systems like gulp, NPM, Webpack, Babel, and the concepts of compiling.
• Keep track of developments in web technology.
• Should be able to handle a team along with multiple clients
• Partner with cross functional teams to ensure projects are completed within the timeline and on budget.
• Translate creative brief into strong conceptual designs.
• Collaborate with the rest of the team members to achieve visual design in scalable digital solutions.
• Solution-oriented and supportive in finding solutions to unexpected challenges.

Experience required.
• Bachelor’s Degree in Software Engineering, Interactive Design or related field.
• 3—5 years of creating well-structured WordPress & WooCommerce custom themes and plugins.
• Strong understanding of PHP, JQuery, MySQL, HTML, and CSS.
• Strong proficiency in JavaScript, including DOM manipulation and the JavaScript object model.
• Strong understanding of WordPress CMS and any PHP based CMS or Framework (Drupal, Joomla, Magento, X-Cart & Laravel, CakePHP, Yii, Codeigniter etc.)
• Thorough understanding of React.js and its core principles or any other JS framework (Angular, Vue, Node).
• Knowledge of modern authorization mechanisms, such as JSON Web Token.
• Must be good with problem solving skills.
• Experience in versioning technologies such as Git/Agile/DevOps environment.
• Experience with continuous integration/Continuous Deployment.
• Knowledge of interacting with RESTful APIs.
• Strong written & verbal communication skills.
• Good analytical and logical skills.
• Understanding the security and compliance aspects of DevOps.

What you’ll get.
• A laptop of your choice.
• A smartphone of your choice with a business mobile plan.
• Monthly one-on-one meetings with a team leader, and structured biannual meetings on professional development.
• Access to a variety of industry-related books, magazines and additional reading materials.
• Ability to modify your daily working hours according to your needs.
• Lots of internal educations from your colleagues & external educations from industry experts.
• Most likely some new friends.

Additional information.

Scellus is an equal opportunity employer and all qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, disability status, protected veteran status, or any other characteristic protected by law.

Tasks

At Mercedes-Benz, we don’t just build cars, we create great software.

We develop tomorrow’s mobility together in our product lines, pushing the digitization of the Mercedes-Benz Group AG forward. As a tech company, we are agile, innovative and always keep our finger on the pulse of change. This is why inner source, FOSS, secure code, DevOps, infrastructure as code (IaC), data analytics, artificial intelligence and many more are core components of our daily work.

IT is our passion, and we move towards a bright future, sometimes quickly, sometimes creatively – but always together.

We believe in integrity, trust and transparency as part of our flexible work culture and a strong emphasis on team work and the learning process, making mistakes and achieving continuous progress together in all products we create and develop within the Mercedes-Benz Group.

Our workplace is anywhere* with a fast connection either remotely at home, at your favorite café or at our integrated office at Wisma Mercedes-Benz that comes with an LRT station at its doorstep, our al fresco cafeteria, ample greenspaces and free parking.

• Collaborative team member with good communication skill used to working in Agile teams

• Growth mindset – enjoy learning

data.job_title: APU - Full Stack Developer - Für frische Absolventen
data.job_description:
Aufgaben

Wir bei Mercedes-Benz bauen nicht nur Autos, wir entwickeln auch großartige Software.

In unseren Produktlinien entwickeln wir gemeinsam die Mobilität von morgen und treiben die Digitalisierung der Mercedes-Benz Group AG voran. Als Tech-Unternehmen sind wir agil, innovativ und immer am Puls des Wandels. Deshalb sind Inner Source, FOSS, Secure Code, DevOps, Infrastructure as Code (IaC), Data Analytics, Artificial Intelligence und vieles mehr Kernbestandteile unserer täglichen Arbeit.

IT ist unsere Leidenschaft, und wir bewegen uns in eine gute Zukunft, manchmal schnell, manchmal kreativ - aber immer gemeinsam.

Wir glauben an Integrität, Vertrauen und Transparenz als Teil unserer flexiblen Arbeitskultur und legen großen Wert auf Teamarbeit und den Lernprozess, Fehler zu machen und gemeinsam einen kontinuierlichen Fortschritt in allen Produkten zu erzielen, die wir innerhalb der Mercedes-Benz Gruppe schaffen und entwickeln.

Unser Arbeitsplatz ist überall* mit einer schnellen Verbindung, entweder von zu Hause aus, in Ihrem Lieblingscafé oder in unserem integrierten Büro in Wisma Mercedes-Benz, das über eine LRT-Station vor der Tür, unsere Cafeteria im Freien, weitläufige Grünflächen und kostenlose Parkplätze verfügt.

Mercedes-Benz Tech Innovation (MBTI) ist Teil des Software-Entwicklerteams von Mercedes-Benz Malaysia Sdn Bhd.

Wir bieten eine Plattform für einen frischen Hochschulabsolventen in unserer Abteilung mit den folgenden Details:

Beschreibung der Aufgabe
• Aufbau einer Karriere in der Softwareentwicklung durch Training on the Job:
• Training am Arbeitsplatz und Erlernen der neuesten Trendtechnologien, die zur Free Open Source Strategie und Politik passen
• On-the-Job-Training und Erlernen von Software-Architekturen als Grundlage für die Software-Realisierung
• Kennenlernen und Erlernen der Agilen Methodik, wie man im Team arbeitet.
• Verständnis für die produktorientierte Denkweise/Kultur
• Hilfe und Unterstützung bei einigen nicht zum Kerngeschäft gehörenden oder nicht funktionsbezogenen Aufträgen/Aufgaben

Qualifikationen
Qualifikationen
• Frischgebackener Hochschulabsolvent mit Abschluss in Informatik / IT oder gleichwertig
• Gute Kommunikationsfähigkeiten
• Guter CGPA von 3,5 und höher
• Gute Kundenservice-Orientierung
• Analytisch, leidenschaftlich und angetrieben von Technologie und Produktqualität
• Gute Lernbereitschaft bei der Entwicklung individueller Fähigkeiten gemäß dem angebotenen Schulungsprogramm
